Deploying a simple application on the command line # Create a simple servlet:
package web.example;
import java.io.IOException; import javax.servlet.ServletException; import javax.servlet.annotation.WebServlet; import javax.servlet.http.HttpServlet; import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest; import javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;
@WebServlet(&quot;/*&quot;) public class HelloServlet extends HttpServlet {
protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) throws ServletException, IOException { response.getWriter().println(&ldquo;Hello world!&rdquo;); } } Package the application into a Web Archive (.war):
helloapp.war +- META-INF
+- WEB-INF
+- web\example\HelloServlet.class
Add the application to your Liberty server:
